# AkekoMi

AkekoMi is a web application built to help educational institutions and teachers manage information about students efficiently. This app allows you to store, retrieve, and update student details, such as names, ages, locations, and universities.

![Student Management App Screenshot](app-screenshot.png)

## Features

- Add new students with their name, age, location, and university.
- View a list of all students currently in the system.
- Search for a specific student by name.

## Technologies Used

- [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/): A modern, fast (high-performance) web framework for building APIs with Python.
- [Python](https://www.python.org/): The programming language used for the backend.
- [Pydantic](https://pydantic-docs.helpmanual.io/): Data validation and parsing using Python data classes.
- [Uvicorn](https://www.uvicorn.org/): A lightweight ASGI server to run the FastAPI application.
- [HTML, CSS, and JavaScript]: Used for the frontend of the web application.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.7 or higher
- FastAPI and Uvicorn (can be installed via pip)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/student-management-app.git
   cd student-management-app
